The relay NEVER signs and NEVER holds a private key. It routes gate-signed holds and
encrypted-display ciphertext to the approver's device and carries the phone-signed decision
back. A compromised relay can at worst cause denial-of-service or spam — never a forged
approval. Grants, consumption, uncertainty, and the timeout receipt are all GATE-signed
(build spec §8) and are intentionally absent from this package's surface (relay ≠ gate).
